-- Lincoln National Increases Quarterly Dividend 50% to 12 Cents
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-11-08T13:10:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-08/lincoln-national-increases-quarterly-dividend-50-to-12-cents.html
Lincoln National Corp. (LNC)  the insurer
that hired Ellen Cooper from Goldman Sachs Group Inc. as chief
investment officer, increased the size of its dividend by 50
percent.  The dividend of 12 cents per share is payable Feb. 1 to
shareholders of record as of Jan. 10, the Radnor, Pennsylvania-
based insurer said today in a statement distributed by PR
Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
 ztracer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
